<Paintings>
  <Text 230 210 20 #000000 0 "Push-pull AB class amplifier">
  <Text 230 270 11 #000000 0 "Use: amplifying current output\nGain: 1\n \nBias of transistors:\n \nInput signal peak to peak Vpp -> 1 V\nOutput current peak to peak -> I_{out} = Input signal/Output resistance = 1V/1k Ohm = 1mA\nBase current -> I_b = 1 mA / 100 = 10uA\nDiode drop -> 0.6 V\nBase current, assuming beta equal to 100 -> Ib = 1 mA / 100 = 10 uA\nCurrent through R1 and R2 -> IR1 = IR2 = 10uA + 1mA = 1.01 mA\nCalculation of R1 = R2 = (12 - (-12) - 0.6*2)/1.01mA/2 = 11.3k Ohm for double side supply\nCalculation of R1 = R2 = (12 - 0.6*2)/1.01mA/2 = 5.35k Ohm for single side supply\n \n \nDC blocking capacitor sizing:\n \nAs a rule of thumb, the capacitance should allow, at the lowest frequency, \nfor Xc to be lower than 1% of the resistance in series:\nXc = 1/(2*pi*f*C) < 0.01*Rout \nC > 1/(2*pi*f*0.01*Rout) = 1/(6.28*1000*0.01*1k) = 15.9 uF -> 22 uF\n \n\nR4 limits current through the transistors">
  <Text 270 760 11 #000000 0 "Power sources">
  <Text 230 1140 11 #000000 0 "Double side supply">
  <Text 230 1780 11 #000000 0 "Single side supply">
  <Text 240 2390 11 #000000 0 "Single side supply">
</Paintings>
